HEADWORD: Delthyris
<hw>Del*thy"ris</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>de`lta</grk> the name of the letter ⟦DELTA⟧ + <grk>thy`ra</grk>
door.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A name formerly given to certain
Silurian brachiopod shells of the genus <er>Spirifer</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Delthyris limestone</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>one
of the divisions of the Upper Silurian rocks in New York.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deltic</ent>⟦br⟧
